    "description": "NSDL Asia Pacific Associates is actively seeking a talented and motivated Risk Analyst to join our dynamic team in Jabalpur. This is an excellent opportunity for professionals who are passionate about making a real impact in a fast-growing organization.\n\nAbout NSDL Asia Pacific Associates:\nNSDL Asia Pacific Associates is a leading organization in the Remote sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Prepare and analyze financial statements, reports, and budgets\n• Prepare MIS reports for senior management review\n• Prepare annual reports and investor presentations\n• Process payroll and manage employee reimbursements\n• Coordinate with external auditors during annual audits\n• Monitor financial performance against targets and provide variance analysis\n• Maintain general ledger and ensure accurate bookkeeping\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Chartered Accountant (ICAI)\n• 0-1 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Forecasting\n• Proficiency in Financial Modeling\n• Proficiency in IFRS\n• Proficiency in QuickBooks\n• Proficiency in GST\n• Proficiency in MS Excel\n• Proficiency in Tally\n• Proficiency in VBA\n\nWork Mode: Remote - Work from anywhere in India\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Transportation and conveyance allowance\n• Maternity and paternity leave\n• Modern office with recreational facilities\n• Company-sponsored certifications\n• Salary Range: 2.5 LPA - 6 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Jabalpur, Madhya Pradesh, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with NSDL Asia Pacific Associates!",
